FBIS4-17402 "drsov079_d_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-079 Daily Report 22 Apr 1994 Regional Affairs Electricity Off Throughout Chechen Republic Electricity Off Throughout Chechen Republic LD2204131194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1027 GMT 22 Apr 94 LD2204131194 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] Staff workers under the Chechen president told INTERFAX that Thursday night electricity was switched off throughout the Republic. Friday morning power remained to be restored. They assumed the Russian joint stock society United Power System moved to punish the Chechen Republic for its failure to square a 12.5-billion ruble debt for electrical power and an 8-billion ruble debt for the delivery of natural gas.
